28/07/2003
WASHINGTON, United States -- In Washington on Saturday (26 July), Serbian Prime Minister Zoran Zivkovic met managers of several US companies, including Boeing, Morgan Stanley and Deloitte & Touche. Zivkovic presented information on investment opportunities and noted interest in expanding bilateral trade co-operation. Following four days in Washington, Zivkovic will travel to New York for talks with UN Secretary General Kofi Annan.
In other news, Serbian police announced on Sunday that they have arrested a member of the Zemun Clan organised crime group. Nikola Bajic, 34, is accused of involvement in the conspiracy to assassinate Zivkovic's predecessor, Zoran Djindjic. Bajic is the fifth-ranked person on the police's most wanted list.
On Sunday, meanwhile, former Yugoslav President Vojislav Kostunica told Reuters that public discontent with the Serbian government would grow over the winter. He predicted renewed calls for early elections in 2004. (Tanjug, B92, Reuters, AFP - 27/07/03)
